Types-of-loops_Some-more_key2: To find the length of an object we can use builtin functions Object.keys() either we can use Object.values().
Types-of-loops_Some-more_key5: Object.keys(objectName) will give you the list of property names.
Types-of-loops_Some-more_key6: So, Object.keys(birds) will give me the list i.e.,
Types-of-loops_Some-more_key7:
[ 'name', 'type', 'ScientificName' ]
And when we use length on it , it gives 3. hooray!…..
Types-of-loops_Some-more_key9: Object.keys(objectName) will give you the list of property names.
Types-of-loops_Some-more_key10: Object.values(objectName) will give you the list of values.
Types-of-loops_Some-more_key13: Object.values(objectName) will give you the list of property values.
Types-of-loops_Some-more_key14: So, Object.keys(birds) will give me the list i.e.,
Types-of-loops_Some-more_key15:
[ 'Bald Eagle', 'Hawk', 'HaliaeetusLeucocephalus' ]
And when we use length on it , it gives 3. hooray!…..
